ZH: 他竟然输给了一个新手。
EN: He actually lost to a beginner.

ZH: 我竟然忘了带钥匙。
EN: I actually forgot to bring the keys.

ZH: 他竟敢对老板发脾气。
EN: He dared to get angry at the boss.

ZH: 竟然下雨了，我的洗衣服没晒干。
EN: It unexpectedly rained, so my laundry didn't dry.

ZH: 她竟然在这么短的时间内成功了。
EN: She actually succeeded in such a short amount of time.

ZH: 他竟然不记得我们的约定。
EN: He actually forgot our appointment.

ZH: 你竟然不擅长游泳？
EN: You actually aren't good at swimming?

ZH: 竟然没人来参加我的生日派对。
EN: Surprisingly, nobody came to my birthday party.

ZH: 他竟然不相信科学。
EN: He actually doesn't believe in science.

ZH: 竟然有人敢挑战老板的权威。
EN: Someone actually dares to challenge the authority of the boss.

ZH: 他竟然让自己迟到了一个小时。
EN: He actually allowed himself to be one hour late.

ZH: 这种事情竟然在我身上发生过。
EN: Such a thing actually happened to me.

ZH: 他竟然把这个秘密告诉了别人。
EN: He actually told someone else this secret.

ZH: 竟然连续下了一个星期的雨。
EN: It actually rained for a whole week.

ZH: 他竟然冒着危险帮助了我的父亲。
EN: He actually risked danger to help my father.

ZH: 竟然能一夜之间变成朋友。
EN: It's actually possible to become friends overnight.

ZH: 她竟然接受了这个荒谬的提议。
EN: She actually accepted this ridiculous proposal.

ZH: 他竟然吃完了一整只披萨。
EN: He actually finished a whole pizza by himself.

ZH: 这个小孩竟然学会了乌克丽丽。
EN: The child actually learned to play the ukulele.

ZH: 竟然还有人相信这种传言。
EN: It's surprising that some people still believe in such rumors.
